Moody's Investors Service Inc said itupgraded 475 mln dlrs of debt of Continental Airlines Inc, aunit of Texas Air Corp.    Raised were the unit's senior secured Denver industrialrevenue bonds to B-1 from Ca and subordinated debt to B-3 fromC.    Moody's said the action recognizes the airline'sreorganization under Chapter 11 of the bankruptcy code, risksassociated with its substantial financial leverage andunpredictable cash flow. Reuter&#3;